        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 8. — Fodinella articulata (Philipps, 1900) n. comb., syntypes NHMUK 1999.3.9.7a, b, Recent, Lifu, Loyalty Island, Sandal Bay. A, group of zooids; B, two ovicellate zooids; C, close-up of the distal part of a zooid showing the ovicell in formation, seven spine bases and the distolateral avicularia with serrated rostrum tips; D, close-up of an orifice showing the beaded anter and proximal mucro. Scale bars: A, 200 μm; B, 100 μm; C, 50 μm; D, 30 μm." ;
